      <span class="headers">PoP: Aid Grimel Quest - For multi-GM tradeskillers</span>
<p>
<b>Quest info is outdated -- fresh update from the site needed before we go live to include info on the baking and final step ...</b><p>
<i>This quest originates in the top of the Plane of Knowledge Library, with Aid Grimel. It requires advanced planar flags for PoP zones, multiple tradeskills over 200 (exact requirements listed below) and, of course, the Planes of Power expansion. At this time, the quest has not been fully completed, so additional details will be added to this page as they become available. Discussion of this quest can be found <a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=76">on the new message boards</a>.</i>
</p>
<p align="center"><a href="#smithing">Part 1: Smithing</a> -- <a href="#brewing">Part 2: Brewing</a> -- <a href="#jewelcraft">Part 3: Jewelcraft</a> --<a href="#pottery">Part 4: Pottery</a> --<a href="#tailoring"> Part 5: Tailoring</a> -- <a href="#fletching">Part 6: Fletching</a> --<a href="#baking">Part 7: Baking</a>
</p> 
<p>After Hailing Aid Grimel, he will mention that he needs someone willing to help him who is a master of trades AND has travelled the planes. In other words, you will need to meet a certain minimum skill level (without any tradeskill improving devices like the various Geerlok tools being taken into account) in a tradeskill AND have been flagged for a certain plane or two for each tradeskill quest he gives you. If you do not have the appropriate planar flag yet, he will reply to you with:</p>
<p>Aid Grimel says 'I am sorry but one who has such limited knowledge of the Planes would not be able to assist me.'</p></blockquote> 
<p>If you have the proper flags, but your skill does not meet the requirement, he will insult your ability in the skill.</p>
<p>This assumes that all combines are done in either a Planar kit of some sort (i.e. Planar Fletching Kit, Planar Sewing Kit, etc) or in a stationary container IN the Plane of Knowledge.</p>
<hr> 
<h4><a name="smithing">Part 1: Smithing</a></h4>
<p>
<b>Skill Requirement</b>: 220 smithing
</p> 
<p>
<b>Flag Requirement:</b> Bertoxxulous AND rescuing Mylik and Adier
</p> 
<p>
Grimel will hand you a breastplate, ask that you wash it, and then coat with a temper and add two Black Diamonds of Nightmares to it. 
</p> 
<p>
Original text: 
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
You say, 'I am well versed in the art of smithing'
</p>
<p>
Aid Grimel says 'Thank you for offering to help _____. Take this breastplate and clean it with a diluted acid wash to get all of the debris out of it. Brew the wash by combining acid and a three celestial essence's. Once the armor is cleaned, coat it with hurricane temper. Finally add two black diamonds of nightmare to the breastplate. This should provide adequate protection for our next journey.' 
</p>
</blockquote> 
<p>
Turn in the finished Breastplate for a Leather Signet. <b>Do not throw away the Leather Signet!</b>
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
Aid Grimel smiles. 'What a wonderful job! Councilman Taldarius shall wear this on our next adventure, I am sure he will find it more protective than his old one. Take this signet as a token of my gratitude. If you are not too busy I have another task, do you have any brewing skill?'
</p>
</blockquote> 
<p>
Leather Signet statistics: 
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
<b><a href="/items/show_item.php?item=9410&menustr=">Hardened Leather Signet</a></b><br />
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <br />
Slot: EAR<br />
AC: 2<br />
STR: +2 &nbsp;&nbsp;STA: +2 &nbsp;&nbsp;WIS: +2 &nbsp;&nbsp;INT: +2 &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
WT: 0.1 &nbsp;&nbsp;Size: TINY<br />
Class: ALL<br />
Race: ALL<br />

</p>
</blockquote> 
<p>
Items given to you by Grimel: 
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
Filthy Breastplate 
</p>
</blockquote> 
<p>
<b>Recipes</b>
</p>
<blockquote> 
<p>
<b>Acid Wash: (Brew barrel, Trivial <= 151) </b><br />
 Jar of Acid <br />
 Celestial Essence <br />
 Celestial Essence <br />
 Celestial Essence 
</p> 
<p>
<b>Cleansed breastplate: (Forge Trivial 227) </b><br />
 Acid Wash <br />
 Filthy Breastplate 
</p> 
<p>
<b>Tempered breastplate: (Forge, Trivial >227 <= 231) </b><br />
 (Cleaned) Breastplate <br />
